For your hobby-tracking app, hereâ€™s a tech stack recommendation based on your requirements:

Frontend:
React.js (Next.js recommended for SEO & performance)
Tailwind CSS (for styling)
Recharts / Chart.js (for data visualization)
PWA Support (to install as an app on mobile/PC)
Backend:
Node.js with Express.js (lightweight & scalable)
Passport.js / Firebase Authentication (for password encryption & Google login)
Database:
PostgreSQL (structured data with relations)
Firebase Firestore / MongoDB (if you prefer NoSQL)
Redis (optional, for caching & fast streak validation)
Hosting & Deployment:
Vercel / Netlify (for frontend deployment)
Railway.app / Render / AWS (for backend & database)
Additional Features:
JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for secure authentication
Cron Jobs (to check and update streaks daily)
